# decision-capture.workflow.list
# Purpose: Route traceflux decisions to Issue vs Docs
#
# Contract:
#   Pre:  Have decision/information to record
#   Post: Stored in correct destination
#   Invariant: Docs stay clean (permanent rules only)
#
# Imported from: workflow-as-list/workflow/decision-capture.workflow.list
# Adapted for: traceflux project

# WHY: Temporary decisions clutter docs
- (classify) Determine destination
  - Ask: Will this be relevant in 6 months? (yes/no)
  - Ask: Is this traceflux-specific or general? (specific/general)
  - Rule: If no OR specific -> Issue (temporary)
  - Rule: If yes AND general -> Docs (permanent)

# WHY: Issues track decisions with discussion
- (create-issue) If temporary:
  - Template: .github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/decision.yml
  - Fields: Context, Options, Rationale, Owner, Review Date
  - Labels: decision, tmp
  - Link: Related files/issues

# WHY: Docs store timeless principles
- (update-docs) If permanent:
  - Target: docs/ directory or README.md
  - Format: Follow prompt-engineering principles
  - Commit: "docs: <summary>"

# WHY: Traceability matters
- (link) Cross-reference
  - Issue -> Link to related docs
  - Docs -> Link to decision issue (in comment)

# WHY: Verify before moving on
- (verify) Confirm recording
  - Issue: Show URL
  - Docs: Show git diff
  - Ask: Correct? (yes/no)

- End
